    <forecast>
        <area aac="SA_FA001" description="South Australia" type="region">
            <forecast-period start-time-local="2026-07-06T04:10:59+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-06T04:10:59+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-05T18:40:59Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-05T18:40:59Z">
                <text type="warning_summary_footer">For latest warnings go to www.bom.gov.au, subscribe to RSS feeds, call 1300 659 210* or listen for warnings on relevant TV and radio broadcasts.</text>
                <text type="synoptic_situation">A high pressure system centred near Tasmania will extend a ridge over SA. The ridge will weaken mid-week as a trough moves over the west and north of SA then a cold front will move across the south late Friday and early Saturday.</text>
                <text type="product_footer">* Calls to 1300 numbers cost around 27.5c incl. GST, higher from mobiles or public phones.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
        <area aac="SA_PW014" description="North East Pastoral" type="public-district" parent-aac="SA_FA001">
            <forecast-period index="0" start-time-local="2026-07-06T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-07T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-05T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-06T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Mostly sunny. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. The chance of morning frost south of Yunta. Winds southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Daytime maximum temperatures between 15 and 19.</text>
                <text type="uv_alert">Sun protection 11:00am to 1:40pm, UV Index predicted to reach 3 [Moderate]</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="1" start-time-local="2026-07-07T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-08T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-06T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-07T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. Slight chance of a shower west of Leigh Creek, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 25 to 35 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 10 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 22.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="2" start-time-local="2026-07-08T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-09T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-07T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-08T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Partly cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. Medium chance of showers north of Leigh Creek, near zero chance elsewhere. Winds east to southeasterly 20 to 30 km/h. Overnight temperatures falling to between 5 and 12 with daytime temperatures reaching between 16 and 21.</text>
            </forecast-period>
            <forecast-period index="3" start-time-local="2026-07-09T00:00:00+09:30" end-time-local="2026-07-10T00:00:00+09:30" start-time-utc="2026-07-08T14:30:00Z" end-time-utc="2026-07-09T14:30:00Z">
                <text type="forecast">Cloudy. The chance of morning fog south of Yunta. High chance of showers north of Leigh Creek, medium chance elsewhere. The chance of a thunderstorm north of Oodnadatta in the afternoon and evening. Winds east to southeasterly 15 to 25 km/h tending south to southeasterly 15 to 20 km/h during the afternoon then becoming light during the evening. Overnight temperatures falling to between 7 and 11 with daytime temperatures reaching between 15 and 19.</text>
            </forecast-period>
        </area>
